This file describes changes to pypersist since the initial release.

0.8 (2019-04-11)
  - Fix a problem with dependencies

0.7 (2019-04-11)
  - Add support for persistent class methods
  - Test suite for Sage

0.6 (2019-02-28)
  - Support for Sage-specific objects
  - Ability to include metadata

0.5 (2019-02-14)
  - Backwards compatibility for Python 2.7
  - Tests for MongoDB caches

0.4 (2019-02-06)
  - Include documentation in PyPI archive

0.3 (2019-02-05)
  - Setup automatic documentation with Sphinx
  - Add module-level docstrings

0.2 (2019-01-29)
  - Initial release (after a hiccup with PyPI)
